text=(:notitle:)%0a(:table valign=top:)%0a(:cellnr colspan=3 width=380 bgcolor=#74483f align=center:)%0a!!%25white%25The Hellriders%25white%25%0a(:cellnr rowspan=30 width=400 align=center:) http://images4.wikia.nocookie.net/__cb20090502015761/whitewolf/images/5/5e/SkullWTF.png%0a(:cellnr width=340 colspan=2 align=center:)%0ahttp://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/images/wtf/headers/wtf_s.png%0a(:cellnr width=150 align=left:)'''Totem:'''%0a(:cell width=190:) Iron-Horse%0a(:cellnr width=150 align=left:)'''Membership:'''%0a(:cell width=190:) 8 Members%0a(:cellnr width=150 align=left:)'''Territory:'''%0a(:cell width=190:) I-95%0a(:cellnr width=150 align=left:)'''Alpha:''' %0a(:cell width=190:) Barricade, Rahu of the Blood Talons%0a(:cellnr width=150 align=left:)'''Position:'''%0a(:cell width=190:) Logistics%0a%0a%0a(:cellnr width=150 align=left:)'''Player:''' %0a(:cell width=190:) NPC: LeeK%0a(:cellnr width=150 align=left:)'''Theme Music:''' %0a(:cell width=190:) [[http://www.youtube.com/ |Music]]%0a(:tableend:)%0a%25%25http://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/images/wtf/headers/wtf_d.png%0a%0aIf you want something moved or need to travel fast you come to the Hellriders. The pack is one of the larger and more influential ones, second only in size to the Dirty Dozen. They also maintain a very fierce rivalry with the Dozen and their leader - Crooked-Grin.%0a%0aThe Hellriders are led by a pair of werewolf brothers. The elder brother is called "Barricade" and is the acting Alpha of the pack. The younger brother is named "Axel" and tends to be the more amiable of the duo. He usually is sent as the emissary of the pack, representing them to the Hegemony.%0a%0aThe pack consists of bikers, street racers, and drifters that wander the highways and streets of Savannah. They primarily claim the long stretch of I-95 as their territory, watching over it as a major supply line for the pack and the Hegemony.%0a%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a%25%25http://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/images/wtf/headers/wtf_h.png%0a%0aThe Hellriders have existed in Savannah since shortly after World War II. They were formed by werewolves who were disenfranchised by the horrors of the second great war and the terrors humanity birthed during that period. There were many werewolves who latched onto the spirit of rebellion that followed in its wake.%0a%0aThey have maintained their territory for nearly a century under the cover of a motorcycle gang. Their dispute with the Dozen has also been just as ancient, involving failed attempts by both packs to absorb the territories of the other during the bloody events of the Brethren War.%0a%0aThey were one of the first packs to voluntarily submit themselves to the Lords of Mourning Glory when they took control. They have a culture centered around the street and most respect those who know how to handle a vehicle and race.%0a%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a%25%25http://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/images/wtf/headers/wtf_rph.png%0a''Supply Line -'' The Hellriders are in charge of logistics for the entirety of the Hegemony. They transport weapons and armor to packs and Wolf-Blooded that need the supplies for the war effort. They are the ones packs must negotiate with to obtain equipment from the Hegemony.%0a%0a''Blood Money-'' The Hellriders are the main pack dealing with the vampires that are currently funding the Hegemony's conflict with Pure Tribes. This comes with some strings attached. The Hellriders may ask PCs to perform tasks such as being leased out as bodyguards to important Kindred VIPs.%0a%0a''Security-'' The Hellriders may need some extra muscle to bring supplies across the city to packs in need. The Pure Tribes are a constant danger to transport of not just weapons, but also necessities like food and water to keep the war effort going.%0a%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a%25%25http://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/images/wtf/headers/wtf_q.png%0a"I'm just the little brother. I'll bring it up to my big brother." - Axel, Emissary of the Hellriders %0a%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a%0a(:include CityBook.WerewolfNavigationBar:)
