 territory, watching over it as a major supply line for the pack and the Hegemony.%0a%3c %0a%3c [[%3c%3c]]%0a%3c %25%25http://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/images/wtf/headers/wtf_h.png%0a%3c %0a%3c The Hellriders have existed in Savannah since shortly after World War II. They were formed by werewolves who were disenfranchised by the horrors of the second great war and the terrors humanity birthed during that period. There were many werewolves who latched onto the spirit of rebellion that followed in its wake.%0a%3c %0a%3c They have maintained their territory for nearly a century under the cover of a motorcycle gang. Their dispute with the Dozen has also been just as ancient, involving failed attempts by both packs to absorb the territories of the other during the bloody events of the Brethren War.%0a%3c %0a%3c They were one of the first packs to voluntarily submit themselves to the Lords of Mourning Glory when they took control. They have a culture centered around the street and most respect those who know how to handle a vehicle and race.%0a%3c %0a%3c [[%3c%3c]]%0a%3c %25%25http://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/images/wtf/headers/wtf_rph.png%0a%3c ''Supply Line -'' The Hellriders are in charge of logistics for the entirety of the Hegemony. They transport weapons and armor to packs and Wolf-Blooded that need the supplies for the war effort. They are the ones packs must negotiate with to obtain equipment from the Hegemony.%0a%3c %0a%3c ''Blood Money-'' The Hellriders are the main pack dealing with the vampires that are currently funding the Hegemony's conflict with Pure Tribes. This comes with some strings attached. The Hellriders may ask PCs to perform tasks such as being leased out as bodyguards to important Kindred VIPs.%0a%3c %0a%3c ''Security-'' The Hellriders may need some extra muscle to bring supplies across the city to packs in need. The Pure Tribes are a constant danger to transport of not just weapons, but also necessities like food and water to keep the war effort going.%0a%3c %0a%3c [[%3c%3c]]%0a%3c %25%25http://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/images/wtf/headers/wtf_q.png%0a%3c "I'm just the little brother. I'll bring it up to my big brother." - Axel, Emissary of the Hellriders %0a%3c %0a%3c [[%3c%3c]]%0a%3c %0a%3c (:include CityBook.WerewolfNavigationBar:)%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
